 Myths of Software Development  (1)<body>
  Myths of Software Development  (1)  
    Myths of Software Development  (1) 

    The only deliverable for a successful project is a working executable program  A working program is only one part of a system that includes all elements of a software product  Discussion: Additional deliverables    Once software is working, maintenance is minimal and can be done ad hoc  To the dismay of many managers, over 50% of budget is typically expended on maintenance  Software maintenance should be organized, planned, and controlled as if it were the largest endeavor within an organization       
 
   

